Another great thing about this rifle is the forged elevated optic rail.  This allows easy instalation of a large objective scope and lets you get a much more comfortable sight picture. postcontent:
New In Package 

Shipping 5.00


item # 34 


The MagPul Back Up Sight (MBUS) Flip-Up Front Sight is a durable, inexpensive Back Up Iron Sight option specifically tailored for the AR-15 platform. Constructed of high impact polymer, the sights are lightweight, unobtrusive, and capable of withstanding harsh environments and rough handling in the field. The Flip-Up Front Sight is spring loaded, popping up instantly when activated by pressing down on either of its side levers or from the top. The sight remains upright under spring and detent pressure, folding only when deliberately stowed by the shooter or in the case of a jarring impact to prevent damage. The MBUS clamps to any standard Picatinny railed handguard, providing the same height-over-bore as a mil-spec A2 fixed front sight. 

The product-improved Gen 2 MBUS Front Sight features a slimmer profile for greater optics compatibility when in the folded position, while the front sight post now incorporates a spring lock for consistent elevation adjustment. 

NOTE: MBUS Front Sights CANNOT be mounted to a railed gas block due to the extreme heat generated during firing. The MBUS Front Sight must be mounted to a railed handguard on the same plane as the receiver rail. MBUS front sights are not compatible with MOE Handguards.

title: For Sale:  YHM/RRA AR-15
postcontent:
For sale is a very nice RRA complete lower and the flagship YHM Specter Black Diamond Carbine Upper. Those who know YHM (Yankee Hill Machine) and RRA (Rock River Arms) know this is not just another AR that has been thrown together and it has some extras. Details on the upper are as follows:

The Diamond forearm bridges the gap between the upper receiver and hand guard and is marked for position on all 4 sides. YHM's diamond pattern in the hand guard reduces weight and blends perfectly with the diamond fluted barrels.

Features Include:
* Forged 7075-T6 Aluminum YHM Flat Top Upper Receiver
* "T" Marked Upper Receiver
* Forward Assist
* 16" 4140 Steel Barrel, Heat Treated to RC 25-32
* Chambered in 5.56 N.A.T.O., Chrome-Lined with either a 1:9" or 1:7" Twist
* YHM Diamond Fluting Improves Rigidity and Aids in Barrel Cooling
* YHM Phantom 5C2 Flash Hider / Compensator (YHM-28-5C2)
* YHM Specter Length Diamond Handguard (YHM-9637-DX)
* YHM Forearm Endcap (YHM-9484-A)
* YHM Low Profile Gas Block (YHM-9384)
* YHM Forearm Mounted Flip Front Sight (YHM-9627)
* YHM Flip Rear Sight (YHM-9680)

This AR also comes with the collapsible Vltor EMOD (Enhanced Modstock) this stock is not just your plain jane collapsible stock! The buttplate of the EMOD is slightly wider and longer at the toe than the regular M4 stock with a noticeable negative pitch, making transitions from the ready feel much more natural. The EMOD was given enough weight to help balance out the normally muzzle heavy feel associated with negative pitch buttstocks. The EMOD features more storage in the removable, waterproof side compartments; the EMOD holds up to four CR123 or three AA batteries. There is also an additional weather proof compartment in the clubfoot area of the stock, this compartment can be accessed quickly and holds two AA batteries or other small parts.

This AR also has the Magpul Rifle Grip as well as the Magpul Vertical Grip in tan. This weapon will come with a 30rd steel mag as I am keeping all of my 30rd Pmags.

I will take $1850 OBO for the AR. My local shop has AR's listed right now much higher than that and lots of them are of lesser quality. Figured I would try to sell it on my own first so number one I dont have to pay them a consignment fee and number 2 someone has the option of purchasing one without paperwork. I also do not mind working through an FFL if that makes you more comfortable. However I will require a valid id or drivers license regardless. At the gun show over the weekend and they were selling AR's for much more than $2500 and Pmags were going for $100 each. I am taking a gamble on selling this one because if this ban does go through and if anyone remembers the Clinton ban knows what these weapons and mags will be worth if they get it pushed through and my feelings are you wont be able to purchase one again without class 3 paperwork.

If you are really serious please feel free to email or call or text REDACTED. As info if this listing is still present then the rifle is still available. Only trades that really interest me would be a Benelli Super Vinci or Wilson Combat 1911's.

title: For Sale:  4 Winchester Model 70 Supergrades...The Nearly-Perfect Rifle Battery
postcontent:
This is a matching set of 4 truly unique limited production Winchester Model 70 Super Grade rifles...each of which is chambered in a cartridge that is ideal for the game animals they commemorate and is so marked with engraving on the magazine floorplate. Only 100 of these sets were made. The Midway Foundation commisioned Winchester to make these rifle sets. The pictures do not do these rifles justice. They are stunning.

Rifle #1 is the Varmint Rifle chambered in the blistering 22-250. Rifle #2 is the Deer/Antelope Rifle chambered in the flat shooting 270 Win. Rifle #3 is the Elk/Moose chambered in the potent 300 Win Mag. Rifle #4 is the Dangerous Game Rifle and is chambered in 375 H&H Mag. All of the classic Model 70 Super Grade features are present โ the fancy grade checkered walnut stock with shadowline cheeckpiece and ebony fore-end tip, the engraved crossbolt head and the traditional Super Grade pistol grip cap. Each of these beautiful rifles is built with the Pre-โ64 style action that offers a forged steel receiver, massive external claw extractor, controlled round feeding and reliable blade ejection. 

Not only did Winchester only make 100 of these 4 rifle sets but...they do not make a Model 70 SuperGrade in 22-250 or 375 H&H Mag. This adds to the value and uniqueness of this set. These rifles are NIB...never been fired. In 2012 one of these sets auctioned for $16,000.00 up in Wyoming in a Wild Sheep Foundation Auction. See link...

http://bid.wildsheepfoundation.org/The-Rifle-Battery_i11637525

I spoke with an official at the Midway Foundation who informed me that these rifles are among the last Model 70 Super Grades that were manufactured in American facilities. Future manufacturing is being moved to Japan. Get the last of the American made Model 70 Super Grades while you can!

title: For Sale:  AR-15 YHM/Rock River Arms
postcontent:
For sale is a very nice RRA complete lower and the flagship YHM Specter Black Diamond Carbine Upper. Those who know YHM (Yankee Hill Machine) and RRA (Rock River Arms) know this is not just another AR that has been thrown together and it has some extras. Details on the upper are as follows:

The Diamond forearm bridges the gap between the upper receiver and hand guard and is marked for position on all 4 sides. YHM's diamond pattern in the hand guard reduces weight and blends perfectly with the diamond fluted barrels.

Features Include:
* Forged 7075-T6 Aluminum YHM Flat Top Upper Receiver
* "T" Marked Upper Receiver
* Forward Assist
* 16" 4140 Steel Barrel, Heat Treated to RC 25-32
* Chambered in 5.56 N.A.T.O., Chrome-Lined with either a 1:9" or 1:7" Twist
* YHM Diamond Fluting Improves Rigidity and Aids in Barrel Cooling
* YHM Phantom 5C2 Flash Hider / Compensator (YHM-28-5C2)
* YHM Specter Length Diamond Handguard (YHM-9637-DX)
* YHM Forearm Endcap (YHM-9484-A)
* YHM Low Profile Gas Block (YHM-9384)
* YHM Forearm Mounted Flip Front Sight (YHM-9627)
* YHM Flip Rear Sight (YHM-9680)

This AR also comes with the collapsible Vltor EMOD (Enhanced Modstock) this stock is not just your plain jane collapsible stock! The buttplate of the EMOD is slightly wider and longer at the toe than the regular M4 stock with a noticeable negative pitch, making transitions from the ready feel much more natural. The EMOD was given enough weight to help balance out the normally muzzle heavy feel associated with negative pitch buttstocks. The EMOD features more storage in the removable, waterproof side compartments; the EMOD holds up to four CR123 or three AA batteries. There is also an additional weather proof compartment in the clubfoot area of the stock, this compartment can be accessed quickly and holds two AA batteries or other small parts.

This AR also has the Magpul Rifle Grip as well as the Magpul Vertical Grip in tan. This weapon will come with a 30rd steel mag as I am keeping all of my 30rd Pmags.

I will take $1850 OBO for the AR. My local shop has AR's listed right now much higher than that and lots of them are of lesser quality. Figured I would try to sell it on my own first so number one I dont have to pay them a consignment fee and number 2 someone has the option of purchasing one without paperwork. I also do not mind working through an FFL if that makes you more comfortable. However I will require a valid id or drivers license regardless. At the gun show over the weekend and they were selling AR's for much more than $2500 and Pmags were going for $100 each. I am taking a gamble on selling this one because if this ban does go through and if anyone remembers the Clinton ban knows what these weapons and mags will be worth if they get it pushed through and my feelings are you wont be able to purchase one again without class 3 paperwork.

If you are really serious please feel free to email or call or text 870-577-4472. As info if this listing is still present then the rifle is still available. Only trades that really interest me would be a Benelli Super Vinci or Wilson Combat 1911's.
